sp.p:
              
              I can have any common charity to such a prayer

              From a friend I would expect a love to prosper in; 

              Without exceptions such a love as might

              Make all my undertakings thankful to it; 

              Precisely just is seldom faithful in our wishes

              To another man's desires: Farewell.

              
              Your sister is my adversaries wife; 

              That nearness needs must consequently draw

              Your inclination to him.

              
              Take him at his word; 

              If he does lose, you are saved by miracle,

              For I never knew a lawyer yet undone.

              
              
                Marry sir even as I was fainting and falling down

                for want of sustenance, the enemy made a shot at me,

                and struck me full in the paunch with a penny loaf.

              
              
                Faith and mine is much about that matter too; 

                your Girdle and Hangers, and your Beaver, shall be sufficient

                bail for it.

div2.stage:
Duboys runs upon Montague, and strugling yeelds him his Sword; 
          the Officers draw, Laverdine and La-poope in the scuffling retire, Montague 
          chaseth them off the Stage, himselfe wounded.

sp.p:
              
              I am your friend and servant,

              Struggle with me and take my Sword; 

              Noble sir make your way, you have slain an Officer.

              
              Yes anywhere; Lackey, take off my spurs; 

              Upon a bridge, a rail but my Swords breadth, upon a battlement,

              I will fight this quarrel.

              
              O Gentlemen, think you I can breath,

              That am restored to the hateful sense

              Of feeling in me my dear husbands death?

              O no, I live not; life was that I left; 

              And what you have called me to, is death indeed; 

              I cannot weep so fast as he doth bleed.

              
              But she will not Madam; 

              For when they talk once, it is like fairy-money,

              They get no more close kisses.

              
              It is all I can do now sweet heart, fair Lady; 

              This to your happy choice brother Amiens,



              You are the man I mean it to.

              
              Give me the Cup, where this health stops, let

              That man be either very sick, or very simple; 

              Or I am very angry; sir, to you; 

              Madam methinks this 
              Gentleman might sit too; 

              He would become the best of us.

              
              Your Lordship does ill to give up your right; 

              I am not capable of this great goodness,

              There sits my wife that holds my troth.
